Reasoning: The paper discusses the application of Dempster Shafer theory to visual recognition, which falls under the sub-category of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of Belief functions and propositional logic also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of an Assumption-based Truth Maintenance System (ATMS), which is a technique used in knowledge representation and reasoning (cs.CR). Finally, the use of Network Reliability techniques suggests a connection to systems and control theory (cs.SY).
